Generous portion of Thai iced teas, and clean and good service.
I will be back--hopefully often but I am always scared of chicken that's of fresh.

We've been going to the Archi's locations for awhile a couple years now and like in any location that we go to, I usually stick to our "usual" (Tom You Shrimp w/ white rice & calamari) because I have a fear called-- disappointment and I hate it.
But I've been trying to get over my fears and one day we decided to venture outside of the usual.
Our newest discovery was the Papaya Salad.
Shredded Papaya with a sweet chili flavor type sauce and leaves of lettuce.
My husband loves spicy food, so he gets (from a scale of 1-10) a 6, as for me, I am a fricking wimp when it comes to heat in my food so, I usually have a few bites and eat the crap out of the lettuce since it's mostly water and it's super refreshing!
Other than the Papaya Salad, the food is like any other Thai restaurant and can assist with any fix that you're looking to get for Thai food.
The thing that differentiates Archi's from other Thai restaurant is the fact that they pay attention to detail through service and presentation.
Pure white plates and carved garnishes are usually small indicators that they care about- presentation.
The decor of the restaurant is very modernized.
Walking towards Archi's the first time, you'd assume that the place was as plain as the exterior of the restaurant... Not at all true.
Boo!
No refills on Thai Ice Tea!!
Some restaurants refill, some don't and Archi's does not.
That's the only reason why I knocked one star off.

