So Archi's turned out to be a hidden gem after going there for the first time, I thought the food was decent but not spicy as I had ordered.
I LOVE spicy food- the hotter, the better.
I know most people think they like spicy food and when you give them a mildly hot dish they start crying like a baby.
Which is why I always order my dishes at the highest spice level a restaurant serves.
And so, my first visit to Archi's I did as such and was disappointed by the lack of heat.
I mentally crossed them off my checklist of my favorite Thai spots....  A month later I was craving Thai and Archi's is literally a block from my house so I gave them another try.
After the first 5 bites of food, I was breathing FIRE!!
I couldn't believe the extreme turn around of spiciness level and I absolutely loved it!
Archi's has now become one of my top favorite Thai places and I know I can count on them to live up to my expectations.
I work in a smoky bar and when I get home from work I usually feel sick to my stomach from breathing in second-hand smoke all day.
