That salad never lets me down..it always turns out really good.
I ventured away from my usual chicken curry dishes and wanted to also order a salad.
I chose the Papaya Salad that had sliced green papaya, tomatoes, green beans, peanuts, dried shrimp, and spicy lime dressing.
When I read it on the menu my eyes failed to see the dried shrimp.
I was picturing nice big juicy shrimps on top of that salad.
When they served it I thought "Maybe I forgot to mention the shrimp" ..because I couldn't see them.
I started eating the salad and my husband starts eating it too.
Then I tasted the little dried up shrimps which are smaller than the peanuts so they are barely noticeable.
I dare not say a word because my husband loathes mostly all seafood and he already ate half of of the dish!
It was a nice crunchy salad because of the papaya but I didn't mind.
If I were to get this again I would have them leave out the dried shrimp because I'm not a fan of it.
I also had my safe Pineapple Fried Rice which has Jasmine rice, stir fried with tomatoes, onion, green onion, pineapples, cashews, raisins, egg and cumin powder.
It's a nice melody of flavor that blends nicely together.
I had to stop myself from taking more than a few bites so I wrapped the rest of it for lunch for the next day.
