Archi's is my current favorite Thai restaurant in town, and I have tried many including Thai Spice, Komol, Lotus of Siam, Thai BBQ, Pin Kaow, Marnee Thai, Promarres, King & I, Panna Thai, Tipps, and Basil 'n Lime.
This is their 3rd and newest location.
We usually get the Pad See-Ew, Pad Thai, Spicy Eggplant, and sometimes a Thai Iced Tea.
My wife also loves their Green Papaya Salad and enjoys their various curry dishes.
For the spicy dishes, they will ask you how spicy you want it on a scale of 0 to 10.
We usually go with "2" because their "3" can be extremely hot, as in sweat-inducing, nose running-like-a-river hot!
I can't even fathom what a "10" might be like.
Their prices are very reasonable except I do get annoyed when they charge you $1 for a small bowl of rice without letting you know ahead of time.
Pet peeve, I know.
What distinguishes this place from most other Thai restaurants (and the original location) is the warm, clean, and contemporary interior.
You feel like you are dining in an upscale restaurant instead of a hole-in-the-wall joint.
Service is typically friendly and efficient.
The combination of quality food at reasonable prices, solid service, upscale ambience, and as an added bonus its proximity to home make this our go to place for Thai.
Well done, Archi, well done.

