Unlike the other Archi's Thai restaurants in Vegas, this one is very very close to my home.
This is a very dangerous thing!
I get, exclusively, the Chicken Panang Curry because it is delicious.
I use Archi's Panang Curry as my bar to which other Thai food is compared.
Pro-tip: they'll ask you if you want spicy level 1-10.
If you're a fan of spicy food, it actually goes to 30 (in increments of 5 after 10).
I get the 30.
It's good.
At the one on S. Rainbow a 30 is *incredibly* and inedibly hot for me.
Here, however, it's only *incredibly* hot, and thus edible.
Different Archi's have different levels once you venture into the land beyond the 1-10 scale.
Tread lightly.
Work your way up.

