Thai food is "hit and miss", and this is a "hit".
This is not exotic, like Lotus of Siam, but it is good, and the portions are generous.
We have compared this place to other Thai places, and also fee that the ingredients are good quality.
We have tried many of the appetizers and our favorite is the the stuffed wing.
I suggest the Papaya Salad and the Panang Curry with Chicken.
I go with a spice level of 5 or 6.
My wife's favorite is the Spicy Basil, spice level 8, but she's Korean.
We have also tried the other noodle dishes, and have been very pleased.
I give them 4 stars, not 5 because the service is fair at best.
You will meet the whole staff being served.
One girl will take your order, another will bring you your food, another will refresh your water or iced tea, another will bring you your check.
Make all your requests at one time, or you may have to hunt down your server.
We find ourselves frequently yelling for a bus boy, which is not considered rude in the Thai Culture.
This place is located next to a Movie House, so I think it's perfect for Dinner and a Movie!!!
Settibello Pizza, Bachi Burger, 808 Hawaiian Tapas is also here.
Skip these places and go to Archi's.
Your taste buds and wallet will both thank you!!

