We also asked for lemons 2 times in a row, the second person finally brought it for us.
There were a lot of servers but no one wanted to help our table.
Our food was getting cold as were were waiting for these things.
The positive things I could take from this place was that the noodles were moist, the pad kee mao had nice flavor, and the pad thai (although bland) was a massive portion - I feel like it was at least 4 portions that they brought out, which is a good deal.
Yet, I wasn't a fan about the horrible service.
If I ever feel inclined to come back, I would order take out instead.
My search for a no fail and delicious thai restaurant close to home continues.

Spur of the moment lunch time stop turned into restaurant love affair!
That's what happened last weekend between Archi's and I.
What a great find!
What I loved immediately about this place was the warm, welcoming interior.
I forgot that I was in a huge strip mall somewhere in Vegas.
My cucumber salad was sweet and refreshing and my chicken was delicious.
The veggies were fresh and tasty.
Our drinks were filled at all times, and we never went without anything we could need or want.
The prices were fair (really good lunch specials during the week, but we were there on a weekend).
I think this is standard everywhere, but it still bugged me that we weren't able to just pay a little extra to upgrade to brown rice (we had to get the steamed rice that came with the meals and then pay for a huge side of brown rice).
If that's my only real complaint about this terrific restaurant then I know I'll be back (but only when I have to be on this side of town).
There's something so exciting about stumbling in to a new place and being totally blown away by it.
I'll be thinking of this restaurant and that meal for quite some time!

The pad Thai was delicious!
We came here when my parents were in town (from the Midwest) and neither have ever really had Thai food before.
They both loved it.
My mom, who hates spicy things, ordered pad Thai with 0 heat.
I forget what my dad ordered, but he asked for a 7 on heat.
Now, my dad has burned most of his taste buds off over the years from eating spicy things, so most things advertised as spicy barely register for him.
He said the 7 was fine, it had some heat, but it wasn't too much.
I didn't see a kids menu and didn't think to ask for one, but my kids, who are fairly picky, ended up eating fried rice with no problems.
I really enjoyed my experience at Archi's and can't wait to go back.

