Archi's is the kind of place that's been around for a while and pats itself on the back for it.
"Authentic" they say.
Service is average.
It's often enough, but mostly present for ordering.
The menu is the "right" size.
It has noodles, curries, and fried rice dishes without overloading you.
This is a stark contrast to so many other Thai restaurants making menus as large as possible.
I think they understand what their customers ask for at Archi's.
They've certainly shown it works by opening so many locations.
Now, the food.
Archi's is the absolute king of noodle dishes in Vegas.
They have my favorite Pad Thai out of any Thai restaurant I've been to ever.
The intensity of the sauce is simply unmatched.
I also enjoy their pad see ew, but Pad Thai is always my first choice.
The portions are also colossal.
You simply can't leave without a full stomach.
As for everything else, you can find better elsewhere.
Their curries are a rip-off.
Full of bamboo shoots for the most part and nothing else.
Fried rice is simply fine and without any qualities a good fried rice should have: salty, oily, and distinct savory flavor.
The spicy basil is strong in basil flavor, but small in portion.
The spicy eggplant is a bit oversauced but otherwise good.
Noteworthy: lunch specials.
They're a great deal particularly if you dine in.
You'll get your item, an egg roll, a side salad, soup, and a little... dough.. thing I can't explain.
Great deal, great price.
Weekdays only.
For Thai-style noodle cravings, there is simply no better choice from my experience.
For everything else, you can surely find alternatives.

